  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen `truffle test` is executed it does not clean up the files it creates in the system temporary directory. It appears that cleanup is attempted between tests of contracts, but is halted when the next test begins. When the final test concludes and `truffle test` exits cleanup appears to be incomplete.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Run `truffle test`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nNo temporary files remain after execution completes.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nA directory exists under the system subdirectory containing many files, all of a regular two-part structure .The first part starts begins and ends with exclamation marks with the middle being a word like blockHashes or trie_db. The second part is an address string in hexadecimal. These files can sum to gigabytes.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- * Operating System: Mac OS X 10.14.6\r\n  * Ethereum client: web3.js 1.2.1\r\n  * Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.0.35\r\n  * node version (`node --version`): 10.16.3\r\n  * npm version (`npm --version`): 6.9.0\r\n- * Operating System: Ubuntu 18.04.3\r\n  * Ethereum client: web3.js 1.0.-beta.37\r\n  * Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.0.12\r\n  * node version (`node --version`): 10.16.1\r\n  * npm version (`npm --version`): 6.9.0\r\n",
